{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841085249,"sessionID":"ses_2879fbe5affeDviCnbLKcjMiQx","part":{"id":"prt_d786072aa001Ujd5QAIbcOyjYw","messageID":"msg_d78606a31001QASADrTUFnw2jv","sessionID":"ses_2879fbe5affeDviCnbLKcjMiQx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_4a72c9e9393d4b1d9299ede8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-003: CRD Shared Types & Constants\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal defines shared types and constants for the `pkg/apis` module to be used across CRDs in the AgentCube project. The goal is to:\n6: \n7: 1. **Centralize common type definitions** - Avoid duplication of types like `ResourceQuota`, `NetworkPolicy`, and lifecycle hooks across multiple CRDs\n8: 2. **Establish naming conventions** - Consistent naming for phases, conditions, and resource types\n9: 3. **Provide reusable validation utilities** - Shared validation functions for common fields\n10: 4. **Enable code generation consistency** - Ensure generated client-go code follows consistent patterns\n11: \n12: ## Scope\n13: \n14: **Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n15: **Language:** Go  \n16: **Size:** S\n17: \n18: This AR covers:\n19: \n20: - **In scope:**\n21:   - Common type definitions in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n22:   - Constant definitions for phases and condition types\n23:   - Shared validation utilities\n24:   - Documentation of patterns for future CRDs\n25: \n26: - **Out of scope:**\n27:   - Changes to existing CRD structures (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n28:   - Client-go code generation changes\n29:   - Controller logic modifications\n30: \n31: ## Current State Analysis\n32: \n33: ### Existing Shared Types\n34: \n35: The codebase already has several types that could be considered \"shared\":\n36: \n37: 1. **`ResourceQuota`** (`types.go:80-90`) - CPU, Memory, Storage limits\n38: 2. **`NetworkPolicy`** / `NetworkRule` (`types.go:102-110`) - Network access rules\n39: 3. **`LifecycleHook`** (`types.go:115-123`) - PreStart/PostStop callbacks\n40: 4. **`ContainerSpec`** (`types.go:125-143`) - Container configuration\n41: 5. **`CodeInterpreterSpec`** (`types.go:79-90`) - Embedded interpreter config\n42: \n43: ### Existing Constants\n44: \n45: 1. **AgentRuntimePhase** constants (`types.go:26-36`):\n46:    - `AgentRuntimePhasePending`\n47:    - `AgentRuntimePhaseRunning`\n48:    - `AgentRuntimePhaseFailed`\n49:    - `AgentRuntimePhaseTerminating`\n50: \n51: 2. **AgentRuntimeConditionType** constants (`types.go:38-48`):\n52:    - `AgentRuntimeConditionReady`\n53:    - `AgentRuntimeConditionSandboxCreated`\n54:    - `AgentRuntimeConditionCodeInterpreterReady`\n55: \n56: 3. **AgentRuntimeCondition** struct (`types.go:50-64`) - Reusable condition pattern\n57: \n58: ### Issues Identified\n59: \n60: 1. **Naming inconsistency**: Types are prefixed with `AgentRuntime` but could be more generic\n61: 2. **No shared validation**: Validation logic in `validation.go:171` for `CodeInterpreter` is specific to that type\n62: 3. **No documentation**: No clear guidelines on which types should be shared vs. CRD-specific\n63: 4. **Tight coupling**: `CodeInterpreterSpec` is embedded in `AgentRuntimeSpec` but may need to be standalone\n64: \n65: ## Proposed Changes\n66: \n67: ### 1. Type Categorization\n68: \n69: Introduce clear categorization for types:\n70: \n71: ```\n72: pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/\n73: ├── types_common.go      # Shared types (ResourceQuota, NetworkPolicy, etc.)\n74: ├── types_agentruntime.go  # AgentRuntime-specific types\n75: └── types_codeinterpreter.go # CodeInterpreter-specific types (if needed)\n76: ```\n77: \n78: **Rationale:** Improves discoverability and makes it clear which types are intended for reuse.\n79: \n80: ### 2. Standardize Type Naming\n81: \n82: Current naming is already consistent with Kubernetes conventions:\n83: - All types use PascalCase\n84: - Related types share prefixes (e.g., `AgentRuntimePhase`, `AgentRuntimeCondition`)\n85: - Embedded structs use descriptive names (`CodeInterpreterSpec`, not just `CodeInterpreter`)\n86: \n87: **No changes needed** - current naming follows Kubernetes API conventions.\n88: \n89: ### 3. Extract Shared Validation\n90: \n91: Create reusable validation functions in `validation.go`:\n92: \n93: ```go\n94: // ValidateResourceQuota validates resource quota fields\n95: func ValidateResourceQuota(quota *ResourceQuota, fldPath *field.Path) field.ErrorList\n96: \n97: // ValidateNetworkPolicy validates network policy configuration\n98: func ValidateNetworkPolicy(policy *NetworkPolicy, fldPath *field.Path) field.ErrorList\n99: \n100: // ValidateContainerSpec validates container specification\n101: func ValidateContainerSpec(spec *ContainerSpec, fldPath *field.Path) field.ErrorList\n102: ```\n103: \n104: **Impact:** Reduces code duplication when adding new CRDs that use these types.\n105: \n106: ### 4. Document Type Usage Patterns\n107: \n108: Add package-level documentation in `doc.go`:\n109: \n110: ```go\n111: // Package v1alpha1 defines the AgentCube runtime API types.\n112: //\n113: // Shared Types:\n114: // Types without AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter prefix are intended for reuse:\n115: // - ResourceQuota: Resource limits and requests\n116: // - NetworkPolicy/NetworkRule: Network access control\n117: // - LifecycleHook: Lifecycle callbacks\n118: // - ContainerSpec: Container configuration\n119: //\n120: // CRD-Specific Types:\n121: // Types prefixed with AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter are specific\n122: // to those CRDs and should not be assumed reusable.\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ### 5. Consider Future CRD Compatibility\n126: \n127: For types that may be used by multiple CRDs:\n128: \n129: **Option A: Keep in v1alpha1 package**\n130: - Simple, no import cycles\n131: - All types in one place\n132: - Risk: Package becomes too large\n133: \n134: **Option B: Extract to `pkg/apis/common`**\n135: - Clearer separation\n136: - Can be imported by multiple API groups\n137: - Risk: Import cycles with scheme registration\n138: \n139: **Recommendation:** Use Option A for now (keep all in `v1alpha1`). Revisit Option B when adding a second API group (e.g., `session.agentcube.volcano.sh`).\n140: \n141: ## Impact Analysis\n142: \n143: ### Files to Modify\n144: \n145: | File | Changes | Impact |\n146: |------|---------|--------|\n147: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Add type usage documentation | Low - documentation only |\n148: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation.go` | Extract shared validation functions | Medium - affects validation tests |\n149: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` | Add comments marking shared types | Low - backward compatible |\n150: \n151: ### Backward Compatibility\n152: \n153: All changes are **backward compatible**:\n154: - No existing type signatures change\n155: - Existing CRDs continue to work\n156: - Generated client-go code is unaffected\n157: \n158: ### Testing Impact\n159: \n160: - Existing unit tests continue to pass\n161: - May add tests for shared validation functions\n162: - No integration test changes needed\n163: \n164: ## Alternatives Considered\n165: \n166: ### Alternative 1: Separate Common Package\n167: \n168: Create `pkg/apis/common/types.go` for shared types.\n169: \n170: **Pros:**\n171: - Clear separation of concerns\n172: - Can be imported by multiple API groups\n173: \n174: **Cons:**\n175: - Import cycles with scheme registration\n176: - Over-engineering for single API group\n177: - More complex code generation setup\n178: \n179: **Decision:** Defer until we have multiple API groups.\n180: \n181: ### Alternative 2: Use Kubernetes Core Types\n182: \n183: Replace `ResourceQuota` with `corev1.ResourceRequirements`.\n184: \n185: **Pros:**\n186: - Standard Kubernetes types\n187: - Better integration with ecosystem tools\n188: \n189: **Cons:**\n190: - `corev1.ResourceRequirements` is more complex than needed\n191: - Loses semantic clarity (our `ResourceQuota` has specific meaning)\n192: - Breaking change for existing CRDs\n193: \n194: **Decision:** Keep custom `ResourceQuota` but document mapping to core types.\n195: \n196: ### Alternative 3: Generate Types from Schema\n197: \n198: Use kube-builder markers to generate types from a schema definition.\n199: \n200: **Pros:**\n201: - Single source of truth\n202: - Automatic validation generation\n203: \n204: **Cons:**\n205: - Significant refactoring effort\n206: - Loss of Go type safety during development\n207: - Complex toolchain setup\n208: \n209: **Decision:** Not justified for current project size.\n210: \n211: ## Implementation Checklist\n212: \n213: - [ ] Add package-level documentation in `doc.go`\n214: - [ ] Add comments to shared types in `types.go`\n215: - [ ] Extract shared validation functions in `validation.go`\n216: - [ ] Update validation tests for extracted functions\n217: - [ ] Document patterns in `deployment/client-go.md`\n218: \n219: ## Future Considerations\n220: \n221: 1. **Multiple API Groups**: When adding `session.agentcube.volcano.sh`, reconsider shared type location\n222: 2. **Webhook Validation**: Move validation to admission webhooks for better error messages\n223: 3. **Defaulting Webhooks**: Consider separate defaulting functions for shared types\n224: 4. **Conversion Webhooks**: Plan for v1alpha1 → v1beta1 migration path\n225: \n226: ## References\n227: \n228: - [Kubernetes API Conventions](https://github.com/kubernetes/community/blob/master/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md)\n229: - [Kube-builder Book](https://book.kubebuilder.io/)\n230: - Deployment spec: `deployment/spec.md`\n231: - Client-go documentation: `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n(End of file - total 231 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-003: CRD Shared Types & Constants\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal defines shared types and constants for the `pkg/apis` module to be used across CRDs in the AgentCube project. The goal is to:\n\n1. **Centralize common type definitions** - Avoid duplication of types like `ResourceQuota`, `NetworkPolicy`, and lifecycle hooks across multiple CRDs\n2. **Establish naming conventions** - Consistent naming for phases, conditions, and resource types\n3. **Provide reusable validation utilities** - Shared validation functions for common fields\n4. **Enable code generation consistency** - Ensure generated client-go code follows consistent patterns\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\nThis AR covers:\n\n- **In scope:**","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775841085211,"end":1775841085247}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841085251,"sessionID":"ses_2879fbe5affeDviCnbLKcjMiQx","part":{"id":"prt_d7860778f001BNnj7XbnVeYwS0","messageID":"msg_d78606a31001QASADrTUFnw2jv","sessionID":"ses_2879fbe5affeDviCnbLKcjMiQx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_c712b054e4c34f72a05f4d6f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   → Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      ↔ Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      → WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         ↔ Redis/Valkey\n33:         → K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775841085215,"end":1775841085249}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841085254,"sessionID":"ses_2879fbe5affeDviCnbLKcjMiQx","part":{"id":"prt_d78608297001U6oUeFUwvP8fGv","messageID":"msg_d78606a31001QASADrTUFnw2jv","sessionID":"ses_2879fbe5affeDviCnbLKcjMiQx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a4d511c409324ceb88ae636e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Design\n2: \n3: Source tree: `/tmp/agentcube-ref` (reference clone). Paths below are relative to repository root unless noted.\n4: \n5: ## Chart.yaml\n6: \n7: | Field | Value |\n8: |--------|--------|\n9: | `apiVersion` | `v1` |\n10: | `name` | `agentcube` |\n11: | `description` | `A Helm chart for AgentCube` |\n12: | `version` | `0.1.0` |\n13: | `appVersion` | `1.0.0` |\n14: \n15: ## values.yaml — full key tree (type & default)\n16: \n17: | Path | Type | Default |\n18: |------|------|---------|\n19: | `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n20: | `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |\n21: | `fullnameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |\n22: | `redis.addr` | string | `\"\"` |\n23: | `redis.password` | string | `\"\"` |\n24: | `router.replicas` | int | `1` |\n25: | `router.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router` |\n26: | `router.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n27: | `router.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n28: | `router.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` |\n29: | `router.service.port` | int | `8080` |\n30: | `router.service.targetPort` | int | `8080` |\n31: | `router.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` |\n32: | `router.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` |\n33: | `router.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` |\n34: | `router.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` |\n35: | `router.config` | object | `{}` |\n36: | `router.extraEnv` | array | `[]` |\n37: | `router.serviceAccountName` | string | `\"\"` |\n38: | `router.rbac.create` | bool | `false` |\n39: | `workloadmanager.replicas` | int | `1` |\n40: | `workloadmanager.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager` |\n41: | `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n42: | `workloadmanager.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n43: | `workloadmanager.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` |\n44: | `workloadmanager.service.port` | int | `8080` |\n45: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` |\n46: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` |\n47: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` |\n48: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` |\n49: | `workloadmanager.extraEnv` | array | `[]` |\n50: | `volcano.scheduler.enabled` | bool | `false` |\n51: | `volcano.scheduler.replicas` | int | `1` |\n52: | `volcano.scheduler.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler` |\n53: | `volcano.scheduler.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n54: | `volcano.scheduler.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n55: \n56: Comments in `values.yaml` state Redis settings “must be provided by the user during installation”; defaults are still empty strings.\n57: \n58: ## Template files (`manifests/charts/base/templates/`)\n59: \n60: ### `workloadmanager.yaml`\n61: \n62: | Kind | Name | Namespace | Notes |\n63: |------|------|-----------|--------|\n64: | `Deployment` | `workloadmanager` | `{{ .Release.Namespace }}` | `replicas`: `workloadmanager.replicas`; `serviceAccountName`: `workloadmanager`; optional `imagePullSecrets`; container `workloadmanager`; image `repository:tag`; `imagePullPolicy`; port `http` → `workloadmanager.service.port`; **env**: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef `metadata.namespace`), `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `REDIS_ADDR`, plus `workloadmanager.extraEnv`; **args**: `--port={{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, `--runtime-class-name=` (empty); **resources**: from values; **liveness/readiness**: HTTP GET `/health` on service port, delays 10s/10s and 5s/5s |\n65: | `Service` | `workloadmanager` | release ns | `type`: `workloadmanager.service.type`; port & `targetPort`: `workloadmanager.service.port`; selector `app: workloadmanager` |\n66: \n67: ### `agentcube-router.yaml`\n68: \n69: | Kind | Name | Notes |\n70: |------|------|--------|\n71: | `Deployment` | `agentcube-router` | `replicas`: `router.replicas`; **conditional** `serviceAccountName` if `router.serviceAccountName` non-empty; optional `imagePullSecrets`; container `agentcube-router`; image from `router.image`; container port `router.service.targetPort`; **env**: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef), `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` = `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, plus `router.extraEnv`; **args**: `--port={{ router.service.targetPort }}`, `--debug`; **resources** from values; **liveness** `/health/live`, **readiness** `/health/ready` on targetPort, 1s initial, 2s period |\n72: | `Service` | `agentcube-router` | `type` `router.service.type`; `port` `router.service.port`, `targetPort` `router.service.targetPort`; selector `app: agentcube-router` |\n73: \n74: ### `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n75: \n76: | Kind | Name | Scope | Notes |\n77: |------|------|-------|--------|\n78: | `ServiceAccount` | `workloadmanager` | release namespace | — |\n79: | `ClusterRole` | `workloadmanager` | cluster | rules below |\n80: | `ClusterRoleBinding` | `workloadmanager` | cluster | binds `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` to `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in release namespace |\n81: \n82: ### `rbac-router.yaml`\n83: \n84: Rendered **only if** `router.rbac.create` is true.\n85: \n86: | Kind | Name pattern | Notes |\n87: |------|--------------|--------|\n88: | `ServiceAccount` | `{{ router.serviceAccountName \\| default \"agentcube-router\" }}` | release namespace |\n89: | `Role` | same as SA name | rules: `secrets` in `\"\"` apiGroup, full verb set `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n90: | `RoleBinding` | same | subject: SA above; `Role` ref same name |\n91: \n92: ### `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n93: \n94: Rendered **only if** `volcano.scheduler.enabled`.\n95: \n96: Creates (in order in file): `ServiceAccount/volcano-agent-scheduler`; `ConfigMap/volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap` with key `agent-scheduler.conf` (actions `allocate`, tiers predicates/nodeorder); `ClusterRole/volcano-agent-scheduler` (large rule set — see RBAC section); `ClusterRoleBinding/volcano-agent-scheduler-role`; `Service/volcano-agent-scheduler-service` (port 8080 metrics annotations); `Deployment/volcano-agent-scheduler` with `replicas` from `volcano.scheduler.replicas`, image from values, args including `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`, security contexts, volumes for config + emptyDir.\n97: \n98: ## RBAC rules (exact apiGroups / resources / verbs)\n99: \n100: ### ClusterRole `workloadmanager`\n101: \n102: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n103: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n104: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxes` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n105: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n106: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxtemplates` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n107: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n108: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n109: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n110: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n111: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/finalizers` | `update` |\n112: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes` | `get,list,watch` |\n113: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes/status` | `update,patch` |\n114: | `\"\"` | `pods` | `get,list,watch` |\n115: | `authentication.k8s.io` | `tokenreviews` | `create` |\n116: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n117: \n118: ### Role `router` (optional)\n119: \n120: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n121: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n122: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n123: \n124: ### ClusterRole `volcano-agent-scheduler` (when enabled)\n125: \n126: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n127: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n128: | `apiextensions.k8s.io` | `customresourcedefinitions` | `create,get,list,watch,delete` |\n129: | `\"\"` | `events` | `create,list,watch,update,patch` |\n130: | `\"\"` | `pods` | `get,list,watch,patch,delete` |\n131: | `\"\"` | `pods/status` | `update` |\n132: | `\"\"` | `pods/binding` | `create` |\n133: | `\"\"` | `persistentvolumeclaims` | `list,watch,update` |\n134: | `\"\"` | `persistentvolumes` | `list,watch,update` |\n135: | `\"\"` | `namespaces,services,replicationcontrollers` | `list,watch,get` |\n136: | `\"\"` | `resourcequotas` | `list,watch` |\n137: | `\"\"` | `nodes` | `get,list,watch,update,patch` |\n138: | `storage.k8s.io` | `storageclasses,csinodes,csidrivers,csistoragecapacities,volumeattachments` | `list,watch` |\n139: | `policy` | `poddisruptionbudgets` | `list,watch` |\n140: | `scheduling.k8s.io` | `priorityclasses` | `get,list,watch` |\n141: | `scheduling.incubator.k8s.io`, `scheduling.volcano.sh` | `podgroups` | `list,watch,update` |\n142: | `\"\"` | `configmaps` | `get,list,watch,create,delete,update` |\n143: | `apps` | `daemonsets,replicasets,statefulsets` | `list,watch,get` |\n144: | `coordination.k8s.io` | `leases` | `get,create,update,watch` |\n145: | `resource.k8s.io` | `resourceclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch` |\n146: | `resource.k8s.io` | `resourceclaims/status` | `update` |\n147: | `resource.k8s.io` | `deviceclasses,resourceslices` | `get,list,watch,create` |\n148: | `shard.volcano.sh` | `nodeshards` | `list,watch,get,update` |\n149: \n150: ## CRD definitions shipped (`manifests/charts/base/crds/`)\n151: \n152: | File | CRD `metadata.name` | group | versions | scope | Notes |\n153: |------|---------------------|-------|----------|-------|--------|\n154: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` | `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` (served+storage); printer column Age | `Namespaced` | `openAPIV3Schema` includes root fields `apiVersion`, `kind`, `metadata`, `spec`, `status`. **spec.required**: `maxSessionDuration`, `podTemplate`, `sessionTimeout`, `targetPort`. **Key spec fields**: `maxSessionDuration` (string, default `8h`); `sessionTimeout` (string, default `15m`); `targetPort` (array of port objects: required `port`, `protocol` enum HTTP/HTTPS, optional `name`, `pathPrefix`); `podTemplate` (annotations, labels, nested `spec` = full PodSpec-shaped schema). **status**: conditions, etc. Annotation `controller-gen.kubebuilder.io/version: v0.17.2` |\n155: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` | `Namespaced` | **spec** includes `authMode` enum `picod|none` default `picod`; `maxSessionDuration` default `8h`; `sessionTimeout` default `15m`; `ports` (same TargetPort shape as above); `template` (image, command, args, env, resources, runtimeClassName, etc.); optional `warmPoolSize` int32. **spec.required**: `template`. **status**: `conditions`, `ready`; subresource `status`. Same controller-gen version annotation |\n156: \n157: ## Dockerfiles\n158: \n159: ### `docker/Dockerfile` (workloadmanager)\n160: \n161: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n162: |-------|------|---------|\n163: | builder | `golang:1.24.9-alpine` | `WORKDIR /workspace`; copy `go.mod`/`go.sum`; `go mod download`; copy `cmd/`, `pkg/`; build `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH} go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\" -o workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` with BuildKit cache mounts |\n164: | runtime | `alpine:3.19` | `apk add ca-certificates`; `WORKDIR /app`; copy binary; `adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver`; `USER apiserver`; `EXPOSE 8080`; `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/workloadmanager\"]`; `CMD [\"--port=8080\"]` |\n165: \n166: Build args: `TARGETOS=linux`, `TARGETARCH` (implicit platform).\n167: \n168: ### `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n169: \n170: Same pattern as workloadmanager builder, plus `COPY client-go/ client-go/`; output binary `agentcube-router` from `./cmd/router`; runtime user `router` UID 1000; `CMD [\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]`.\n171: \n172: ### `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n173: \n174: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n175: |-------|------|---------|\n176: | builder | `golang:1.24.4` | `WORKDIR /app`; copy mod files; download; `COPY . .`; build `picod` from `./cmd/picod` with `CGO_ENABLED=0` |\n177: | runtime | `ubuntu:24.04` | `apt-get install -y python3`; `WORKDIR /root/`; copy binary; **runs as root** (comment: chattr on pubkey + sandbox permissions); `ENTRYPOINT [\"./picod\"]` |\n178: \n179: ## Makefile — variables (key)\n180: \n181: | Variable | Default / definition |\n182: |----------|----------------------|\n183: | `HUB` | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` |\n184: | `TAG` | `latest` |\n185: | `PROJECT_DIR` | directory of Makefile |\n186: | `GOBIN` | from `go env` |\n187: | `CONTAINER_TOOL` | `docker` |\n188: | `SHELL` | `/usr/bin/env bash -o pipefail` |\n189: | `LOCALBIN` | `$(shell pwd)/bin` |\n190: | `CONTROLLER_GEN` | `$(LOCALBIN)/controller-gen` |\n191: | `GOLANGCI_LINT` | `$(LOCALBIN)/golangci-lint` |\n192: | `CONTROLLER_TOOLS_VERSION` | `v0.17.2` |\n193: | `GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION` | `v1.64.1` |\n194: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` | `workloadmanager:latest` |\n195: | `ROUTER_IMAGE` | `agentcube-router:latest` |\n196: | `PICOD_IMAGE` | `picod:latest` |\n197: | `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `\"\"` |\n198: | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` | `agentcube-e2e` |\n199: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_REPO` | `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox.git` |\n200: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION` | `main` (Makefile comment; E2E script overrides — see CI design) |\n201: \n202: ## Makefile — targets\n203: \n204: | Target | Depends / notes |\n205: |--------|-----------------|\n206: | `all` | → `build` |\n207: | `help` | awk help from `##` comments |\n208: | `gen-crd` | `controller-gen`; `crd paths=./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` → `manifests/charts/base/crds` |\n209: | `generate` | `controller-gen object` + `gen-crd` + `go mod tidy` |\n210: | `gen-client` | `bash hack/update-codegen.sh`; `go mod tidy` |\n211: | `gen-all` | `generate` + `gen-client` |\n212: | `gen-check` | `gen-all` then `git diff --exit-code` |\n213: | `build` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` |\n214: | `build-agentd` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd` |\n215: | `build-router` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/agentcube-router ./cmd/router` |\n216: | `build-all` | `build` + `build-agentd` + `build-router` |\n217: | `run` | `go run ./cmd/workload-manager/main.go --port=8080 --ssh-username=sandbox --ssh-port=22` |\n218: | `run-local` | same with `--kubeconfig=${HOME}/.kube/config` |\n219: | `run-router` | `go run ./cmd/router/main.go --port=8080 --debug` |\n220: | `clean` | `rm -rf bin/` and root binaries |\n221: | `deps` | `go mod download`; `go mod tidy` |\n222: | `update-deps` | `go get -u ./...`; `go mod tidy` |\n223: | `test` | `go test -v ./...` |\n224: | `fmt` | `go fmt ./...` |\n225: | `vet` | `go vet ./...` |\n226: | `lint` | `$(GOLANGCI_LINT) run ./...` |\n227: | `gen-copyright` | `hack/update-copyright.sh` |\n228: | `install` | `build` + `sudo cp bin/workloadmanager /usr/local/bin/` |\n229: | `docker-build` | `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE) .` |\n230: | `docker-buildx` | buildx linux/amd64,arm64 |\n231: | `docker-buildx-push` | requires `IMAGE_REGISTRY`; buildx `--push` |\n232: | `docker-push` | tag+push workloadmanager |\n233: | `kind-load` | `kind load docker-image $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE)` |\n234: | `docker-build-router` / `docker-buildx-router` / `docker-buildx-push-router` / `docker-push-router` / `kind-load-router` | same pattern for router image |\n235: | `docker-build-picod` / `docker-buildx-picod` / `docker-buildx-push-picod` / `docker-push-picod` | same for picod |\n236: | `controller-gen` / `golangci-lint` | download via `go-install-tool` macro |\n237: | `e2e` | `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n238: | `e2e-clean` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n239: | `build-python-sdk` | copy `LICENSE` to `sdk-python`, `python3 -m build` in `sdk-python`, remove copied LICENSE |\n240: \n241: ## hack/ scripts\n242: \n243: | File | Purpose |\n244: |------|---------|\n245: | `hack/update-codegen.sh` | Runs `k8s.io/code-generator` **v0.34.1**: sources `kube_codegen.sh`, calls `kube::codegen::gen_client --with-watch --output-dir client-go --output-pkg github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go --boilerplate hack/boilerplate.go.txt --one-input-api runtime/v1alpha1` on `pkg/apis`; post-processes lister files with `sed` to append `.GroupResource()` for codeinterpreter/agentruntime resources |\n246: | `hack/update-copyright.sh` | Prepends Apache/Volcano boilerplate to `*.go` and `*.py` under git root (excluding vendor/venv) if missing “Copyright The Volcano Authors”; uses `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` / `hack/boilerplate.py.txt`; requires `sponge` (moreutils) |\n247: | `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` | Go file header template |\n248: | `hack/boilerplate.py.txt` | Python file header template |\n249: \n250: ## Helm / E2E reference command (from `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n251: \n252: Illustrative install used in E2E:\n253: \n254: ```bash\n255: helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n256:   --namespace \"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n257:   --create-namespace \\\n258:   --set redis.addr=\"redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n259:   --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n260:   --set workloadmanager.image.repository=\"workloadmanager\" \\\n261:   --set workloadmanager.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n262:   --set-json 'workloadmanager.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"},{\"name\":\"JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE\",\"value\":\"agentcube\"}]' \\\n263:   --set router.image.repository=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n264:   --set router.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n265:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n266:   --set router.serviceAccountName=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n267:   --set-json 'router.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"}]' \\\n268:   --wait\n269: ```\n270: \n271: Images are expected to be loaded into Kind with local names `workloadmanager:latest`, `agentcube-router:latest`, `picod:latest` after `make docker-build` variants.\n\n(End of file - total 271 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Design\n\nSource tree: `/tmp/agentcube-ref` (reference clone). Paths below are relative to repository root unless noted.\n\n## Chart.yaml\n\n| Field | Value |\n|--------|--------|\n| `apiVersion` | `v1` |\n| `name` | `agentcube` |\n| `description` | `A Helm chart for AgentCube` |\n| `version` | `0.1.0` |\n| `appVersion` | `1.0.0` |\n\n## values.yaml — full key tree (type & default)\n\n| Path | Type | Default |\n|------|------|---------|\n| `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n| `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/design.md","time":{"start":1775841085224,"end":1775841085252}}}}
